 ancient Egypt and Nubia to the Zulu Kingdom almost two thousand years later. Each chapter is written by a leading historian, interweaving political and social history and drawing on a rich array of sources, including oral histories and recent archaeological findings. Great Kingdoms of Africa is a timely and vital book for anyone who wants to expand their knowledge of Africa's rich history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Africa / General.2bisacsh1 aAdjaye, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBelcher, Wendy Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDooling, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFromont, Cécile, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGwadabe, Muhammadu Mustapha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIdrissa, Rahmane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOjo, Olatunji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTegegne, Habtamu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWengrow, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052039568840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520395688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520395688/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles